	   <h2>About me</h2>
	<p>
       	I am Trinh Tuan Phong, the third-year Ph.D. student <br/> 
in <a href="http://www.math.univ-paris13.fr/" target=_top> Department of  Mathematics </a>, University of Paris 13, France.<br/>
I am working under the supervision of Prof. <a href="http://www.math.jussieu.fr/~klopp/" target=_top>Frédéric Klopp</a> on random Schr&#246dinger operators.<br/>
More precisely, I studies decorrelation estimates for the discrete Anderson model and the lattice Hamiltonian with off-diagonal disorder.<br/> 
My CV is available <a href="cv.pdf"> here </a>.
	</p>
